import java.util.Stack;

public class ParenthesesCounter {
    public static int countValidParentheses(String input) {
        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();
        int validCount = 0;

        for (char c : input.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') {
                stack.push(c);
            } else if (c == ')') {
                if (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() == '(') {
                    stack.pop();
                    validCount++;
                } else {
                    // Mismatched or unbalanced parenthesis
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        return validCount;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String testInput = "((()))(())(()";
        System.out.println("Number of valid parentheses: " + countValidParentheses(testInput));
    }
}
```

This code will count the number of valid pairs of parentheses in the given string. It uses a stack to ensure that each opening parenthesis has a corresponding closing one. If it finds a mismatch or an unbalanced parenthesis, it breaks out of the loop early.

